<center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7667">Euriped</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unekoken.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nekoken</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 6:59:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12154.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So what killed me in FV?</span><hr size=1> Seeing through sneak:<br>
<br>
Some high level mobs have a greater chance of discovering you the longer you are behind them and the closer they are.  If you just stealthily creep by some nasty from behind then you don't usually have a problem.  If you get right behind a mob and just stay there for awhile they may eventually see through sneak.  Note: this is not due to the mob turning around randomly and happening to see you.  For an example be a low-level KoS to the Scouts of Tunare in Kelethin and stand right behind one for a few minutes with hide/sneak on.  Odds are you'll be one-shot killed within 5 minutes by the scout in front of you.  This test was still valid in June when last I was screwing around with testing sneak.<br>
<br><br><br>
This is actually a *feature*.  Long ago I wasted many an hour studying hide, hide/sneak and just plain sneak trying to determine the rhyme or reason behind why they sometimes fail.  It was explained to me by Verant, don't remember if it was Abashi or McQuaid, that there were timed interval checks against sneak and hide with dependencies on the level of the mob and the type of the mob.  This was so long ago that I can't even remember if it was on whineplay or on usenet.  I'm thinking it was usenet.  You should actually be able to look up some of it on a newsgroup search on google.  I believe I also posted the results of those conversations here in the Safehouse about a year and a half ago.<br>
<br>
There's also a number of mobs who have the /con flag screwed up.  Even though they don't see you they still con ready to attack.  This actually used to be far more prevalent with zones such as the old Befallen pre-Kunark where everything pretty much scowled even though nothing could see you.<br>
<br>
On another sneak/hide note: Recently I've noticed that sneak/hide no longer breaks when you pick something up off of the ground.  I'm not quite sure when this changed because it definitely used to break it.<br>
<br>
&lt;Narsse Nekoken of Rodcet Nife&gt;<br>
