<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Every</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mob in the game <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> see you when you sneak <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> in</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> its line of sight. Mobs with see invis <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> see you if you sneak and hide in front of it. Even if you are sneaking, hiding, or both if your in front of a mob that sees invis..... sneaking, hiding, or both is useless. The whole point of sneak is to allow you to stay hidden while moving AND to sneak behind mobs that see invis to get past them.<br>
<br>
When sneak is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> active</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in the line of sight, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> no</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mob in the game can see a rogue. If it does, either you moved into the mobs line of sight, or it moved to a position that made you enter its line of sight, or something made you drop sneak.(Lag will do this at times and also various bugs in the game) Also note that if you are on a mobs hate list its friends will see you, sneaking, hidden, or not.<br>
<br>
*Nothing includes: mobs with see invis, mobs without see invis, dogs in Dreadlands, dogs in Karnors, dogs in Chardok, Drachnid Web-lurker, Sonic bats, any mob in PoF, any mob in PoH, Venril Sathir, Innoruuk, Yelinak, Undead of any kind, etc, etc........nothing, nada, none.<br>
<br>
I would like to add that I have personally seen a mob cast see invis on other mobs. It happens with the shamans/wiz frogs near the Sebilis zone in. If you see the frogs get cleared then sit there and wait for them to respawn. Once they respawn you will be able to sneak/hide past them. After awhile the shamans/wiz will see invis themselves and now they scowl when using sneak/hide <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> unless</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you are behind them with sneak activated. Wait a bit more and you hear them cast again, the warrior frog near it who wasn't scowling a few seconds before is now scowling.<br>
