<br>
IF a mob casts see invis on itself or on others (which they ARE capable of doing, they just don't do it much) then they will see your hide, no matter what level they are, no matter what level you are. There are many many monsters in norrath (and I suppose on luclin now as well) who have an innate 'see invis'. These monsters become less and less of a threat to a rogue as you level. A perfect example of this are the caster sarnaks in chardok. I'm level 57 and I dont 'even really con them anymore, Sarnak's just can't spot me. At that same time, there are mobs who will get an innate see invis check and WILL see you, a great example of this are the ANY dog in KC or the chokidais in Chardok ... not every one will see you, but they'll get a chance.<br>
<br>
Nothing can detect a sneaking rogue. I've had occasion to con both Innoruuk and VS while sneaking and behind them, and they both scowled ... I dont' know if they would have attacked, but honestly, I would still consider it 'nothing' if boss mobs and @#%$ mobs and the like could pick you up ... I mean seriously, you shouldn't be able to pick Innoruuk's pocket. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushariin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shariin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 10:07:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12154.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All drolvargs see through sneak, eh?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Nothing can detect a sneaking rogue.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Incorrect. Go and stand behind Broon some time.  Not only will he scowl, but he will turn around and swing at you!<br>
<br>
You can sneak past gods and dragons, true; it's random other mobs in Norrath that are dangerous. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiuldiin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iuldiin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/01 11:04:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12154.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All drolvargs see through sneak, eh?</span><hr size=1> I think the simple explanation for why things see through sneak is...<br>
<br>
Someone in Verant forgot to define what was 'behind' the mob, so it thinks everything is in front of it, so sneak don't work... <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42094">
-Iuldiin</a> <a href="http://www.relinpor.com"><br>Rel In Por </a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaabumen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aabumen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 3:24:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12154.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: All drolvargs see through sneak, eh?</span><hr size=1> Clue:<br>
<br>
Sneak has zero to do with being 'seen'. Sneak simply reduces agro range. And 'conning' a mob is no guarantee, when sneaking+hiding. Go try Hate sometime ;)<br>
<br>
So if you want, you could say nothing 'see's thru sneak, even @#%$ mobs. But get close enough and a level 1 panzy mob will notice you and agro or not based on other parameters.<br>
<br>
To be precise, when sneak is active, in the 120 degree arc directly in front of the mob (i.e where it is facing, and 60 degrees right and left of that line), the agro range is 'greatly reduced'. How much is 'greatly'? *shrug* it's hard to define, but most reading here already know from experience. Beyond that 120 degree arc, the agro range is redude a *lot* more than in front of it. Like you almost have to touch the mob. A few paces at most (giant mobs are kinda wierd on this fact...real close isn't all that close, heh)<br>
<br>
Hope this clears things up some. And hide is a whole different ballgame. Duh.<br>
<br>
Oh, and D0mn...Hide has no skill checks. Period. Level is irrelevant. Level of mob *or* your level. You can, and many many have, take a rogue, level 1, halfling, worshipper of Brell, and waltz your halfling butt down to the bottom of the Hole. (Caveat: yeah, I know..nothing is perfect. Mobs con kos when they arent, and vice-versa, in the Hole...and some mobs there see thru hide, etc.) The few mobs that see thru Hide are often on Brell faction, so it's not all that hard in most places there. But my point is that its not like a non-brell Mob that cannot see thru Hide will all of a sudden pop me when I waltz near it as a level 1 Brell halfling rogue, just because my 'Hide' skill is at 1 or whatever or because I am level 1 and the mob is level 54. Level of mob, level of player and skill level of either sneak or hide are irrelivant on the success of the Hide. It's all up to whether or not the mob has been coded by verant to see thru Hide (i.e. see invis) and if you are too close/in the wrong position, etc.<br>
<br>
Anywhoo, I've beaten this explanation to death. Next?.... <p><table border=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=420>
